Package: MRcMLhd
Type: Package
Title: Mendelian Randomization via Constrained Maximum Likelihood (High-Dimensional)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Yang", "Liu", email = "liu02528@umn.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements the high-dimensional version of the MRcML
    (Mendelian Randomization via Constrained Maximum Likelihood) method.
    Traditional MR methods rely on a small set of strong instrumental
    variables (IVs), which can be statistically unstable and underpowered
    when genome-wide significant SNPs are scarce. This package generalizes
    MRcML to a high-dimensional regime, where a large number of weak IVs
    are incorporated to recover more genetic information and improve
    statistical power. Invalid-IV selection remains consistent despite
    aggregate weak-IV fluctuation, and the estimator is shown to be
    consistent and asymptotically normal.
